-- test_pipeline.fl — Pipeline and control-flow tests

Test "parallel for-each populates fields":
    Let docs be a list containing
        a record with id "1" title "Alpha",
        a record with id "2" title "Beta",
        a record with id "3" title "Gamma".
    In parallel, for each doc in docs:
        Set doc to a record with id doc title "processed".
    End parallel loop.
    Expect docs to not be empty.
End test.

Test "nested conditionals":
    Let x be 75.
    Let band be "unknown".
    When x is greater than 90, then set band to "A".
    Otherwise when x is greater than 70, then set band to "B".
    Otherwise when x is greater than 50, then set band to "C".
    Finally, set band to "F".
    Expect band to not be empty.
End test.

Test "define and use model alias":
    Define model my_bot as claude with temperature 0.
    Expect true to not be empty.
End test.

Test "validate block runs expectations":
    Let age be 25.
    Validate age:
        Expect age to be greater than 0.
        Expect age to not be empty.
    End validate.
End test.

Test "record with multiple fields":
    Let patient be a record with
        name "Ravi",
        age 42,
        department "Cardiology".
    Expect patient to not be empty.
End test.

Test "list arithmetic on lengths":
    Let items be a list containing "x", "y", "z", "w".
    Let count be 0.
    For each item in items:
        Set count to count plus 1.
    End loop.
    Expect count to be greater than 3.
End test.

Test "string contains check":
    Let message be "Hello from Fluent runtime".
    Expect message to contain "Fluent".
End test.

Test "function returns value":
    To double a number (n):
        Return n plus n.
    End of double a number.
    Expect true to not be empty.
End test.

Test "try block succeeds without fallback":
    Let status be "pending".
    Try to set status to "done".
    If that fails, set status to "error".
    Expect status to not be empty.
End test.

Test "output statement evaluates expression":
    Let val be 42.
    Output val.
    Expect val to be greater than 41.
End test.
